What happened?! I've been ordering from 3 Luigi's for almost a decade and it's been some of the best pizza in the neighborhood but our last two orders in the last month have just been completely off! The dough is not the same, lacking sauce, and the pizzas just aren't coming out the same way they have been for years... Was there a change in management or chef or recipe? The past two experiences have really ruined my trust in this spot 💔

Small, cheap place with a good selection for sit-down dinner or pizza-to-go.  I got oil and garlic pasta on fettuccine. First, the pasta was extremely dry and rather undercooked. It tasted rubbery. Nor did I taste much  garlic in the sauce -- just a few cloves plopped in there. It was very, very bland.  You can customize your pasta with any type of noodle, not something you find many places.  They only take debit and credit so I had to run back to my place. Not a big deal.  The guy who serviced me (see what I did there) was nice, none of the jerkiness I encounter at chain stores here.  I generally prefer these low-key, no-frills, no attitude place to the bougey ones sprouting all around it. This dish was lazy.

The Pizza at 3 Luigi's is probably the best of the many Pizza options in the Fort Greene, Clinton Hill Neighborhoods. You can buy by the slice and it is always really good. Il Porto on Washington by the Navy Yards may have nicer ambiance, but pizza quality wise, you won't go wrong with 3 Luigi's.
